Future Healthcare mission is to provide clients with the best conditions for health, life, and well-being, through a digital ecosystem that connects clients, healthcare providers, and Health and Life insurers. We aim to be a global reference for the provision of services, positioning ourselves as a Client-centric Life and Health Facilitator. We have 5 lines of business that can be provided on an individual, supplementary, or global basis, which are Operations, Technology, Risk Management, Distribution and Digital Health.




We are currently reinforcing the, IT unit, and we are looking for a Junior Data Scientist (m/f) to join our team.




Key responsibilities

•Interact closely with the architect /systems analyst to understand the software requirements, participating in data model solution design;

•Design and develop Machine learning algorithms;

•Gather and interpret business requirements to build and improve existing Machine learning algorithms.




The profile we are looking for...

•Degree in Software Engineering, Quantitative Sciences or similar (or have equivalent professional experience);

•Knowledge in Machine Learning algorithms (supervised and unsupervised);

•Knowledge of Python programming language;

•Knowledge of common Machine Learning tools and libraries (ex: Sklearn, TensorFlow, Pytorch);

•Knowledge of SQL is a plus;

•Good analytical/critical skills and likes to build solutions in the right way and not just something that works;

•Excellent organization skills;

•Team spirit, initiative and good communication skills;

•Experience with agile methodologies;

•Fluency in English.




SEND US YOUR CV! recrutamento@future-healthcare.eu

